cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with image classification and segmentation tasks using handcrafted features and deep transfer learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks and transfer learning indicates that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image retrieval and information retrieval, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for traffic management, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.RO (Robotics and Automation).
